Paul Qureshi wrote:

>Hi all.
>
>I spotted this interesting bit of news on Slashdot. You can find
>information on an open source DirectX to OpenGL wrapped here:
>
>http://www.v3x.net/directx/
>
>The creators are asking for help in porting to Linux and MacOS, although
>I don't think an Amiga port is out of the question! It could be useful
>to some people, and helpful when porting games. I'm not sure about the
>licencing terms for commercial use (hi Hyperion :)
>

Already had a look at it. It seems to be pretty complete, including 
D3DX, but restricted to the DX8 interfaces. Most of the code you will 
encounter during porting is DX6 or DX7, which is completely incompatible.

It seems however that the platform-dependent part is really tiny, so 
porting this to MiniGL or Mesa should be fairly straightforward. The 
performance is still a question, though... A rewrite from DX to 
OpenGL/Warp3D will invariably be faster.

Regards,

